cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.SE 

This paper deals with concurrent programs and presents a logic for reasoning about them. The use of separation logic and the verification of a concurrent counter algorithm suggest that the paper is likely to be in the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) or Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The use of probabilistic reasoning suggests that it could also be in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the fact that the results have been mechanized in Coq suggests that it could also be in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
